First install the version of synclient found here: https://github.com/felipejfc/xserver-xorg-input-synaptics.

Install xdotool - run 'sudo apt-get install xdotool'

To install: clone the project, cd into the directory and run 'make install', then restart X.

A daemon process that interprets swipes
    currently works with
        *three finger swipe left goes back on a webpage (triggers alt+Left)
        *three finger swipe right goes forward on a webpage (triggers alt+Right)
        *four finger swipe up shows or hides desktop (triggers ctrl+alt+d)
        *four finger swipe down opens a terminal (triggers super+t)
